WEBVTT

00:07.507 --> 00:09.051
Previously on
<i>"The Girl from Plainville"...</i>

00:09.051 --> 00:10.677
- You have to say the first
thing that pops into your head.

00:10.677 --> 00:11.970
It's a word game.

00:11.970 --> 00:15.057
- Disney.
- Princess.

00:15.057 --> 00:17.142
- Pretty.

00:17.142 --> 00:20.020
At 6:25 p. m.,
<i>he tells her, "Almost there."</i>

00:20.020 --> 00:22.314
<i>She says, "Okay,"</i>
<i>then three hours later,</i>

00:22.314 --> 00:25.692
<i>"Please answer me.</i>
<i>I'm scared.</i>

00:25.692 --> 00:27.319
<i>I thought</i>
<i>you actually did it."</i>

00:27.319 --> 00:28.779
So what do you want?

00:28.779 --> 00:31.198
- A warrant for her phone.

00:31.198 --> 00:33.659
Bring me something
<i>that can prove intent,</i>

00:33.659 --> 00:35.035
<i>contradiction,</i>
<i>even a cover-up.</i>

00:35.035 --> 00:36.453
<i>Then we'll talk.</i>

00:36.453 --> 00:38.580
- When he went missing,
she was, like, freaking out.

00:40.123 --> 00:41.416
- Missing?

00:41.416 --> 00:43.502
- Yeah, he was missing
for, like, three days.

00:43.502 --> 00:45.587
- She was texting us
the whole time.

01:45.272 --> 01:46.815
- That's cold.

01:46.815 --> 01:48.025
- Not anymore.

01:51.194 --> 01:53.405
- Huh.

01:53.405 --> 01:55.949
- Rayburn, Sutter wants you.

02:05.042 --> 02:07.085
Morning, sir.
Gordon.

02:07.085 --> 02:09.588
- Katie,
what's your thoughts on this?

02:09.588 --> 02:11.798
Gordon, fill her in.

02:11.798 --> 02:15.093
Okay, Michelle Carter,
17-year-old girl,

02:15.093 --> 02:17.387
texts her friends
for three days telling them

02:17.387 --> 02:19.514
her boyfriend's missing,
maybe dead.

02:19.514 --> 02:21.642
Nobody can find him.
She's panicked.

02:21.642 --> 02:24.853
Only thing is, he's not.
- Not what?

02:24.853 --> 02:26.438
- Not missing.
- Well, where is he?

02:26.438 --> 02:28.273
- At home for three more days.

02:28.273 --> 02:29.983
- What happens
after three days?

02:29.983 --> 02:31.318
- He killed himself.

02:33.111 --> 02:35.030
But this girl knew
he wasn't missing or dead.

02:35.030 --> 02:38.116
She was in contact with him
the whole time.

02:38.116 --> 02:40.619
- You think she knew
he was gonna kill himself?

02:40.619 --> 02:44.623
- They were texting about it
for months, weeks, days, hours,

02:44.623 --> 02:46.416
right up until the point
that he actually did it.

02:48.001 --> 02:49.294
She was telling him to do it.

02:51.380 --> 02:53.298
Encouraging him.

02:53.298 --> 02:54.549
- You talk to her?

02:54.549 --> 02:56.426
Talked to her friends.

02:56.426 --> 02:59.012
Look, her story seems
inconsistent.

03:00.514 --> 03:03.058
I think we've got
a manslaughter charge here.

03:04.142 --> 03:06.561
This kid has
a history of depression.

03:06.561 --> 03:09.856
Years on SSRIs, hospital stays,

03:09.856 --> 03:12.234
swallowed a bottle of Tylenol
two years ago.

03:12.234 --> 03:14.111
Seriously, Gordon--
- Once you read the texts

03:14.111 --> 03:15.487
between these two,
you're gonna get it.

03:15.487 --> 03:17.614
Also, I got his phone records

03:17.614 --> 03:19.908
from the boy's mom,
and there are two phone calls

03:19.908 --> 03:22.285
between the two of them
from that night.

03:22.285 --> 03:24.287
- Yeah, well,
even if I get you a warrant,

03:24.287 --> 03:25.455
they're not gonna give you

03:25.455 --> 03:26.748
a transcript
of their phone call.

03:26.748 --> 03:28.041
- Yes, but there's gotta be

03:28.041 --> 03:29.042
more communication
between them,

03:29.042 --> 03:30.460
and the only way I can get it

03:30.460 --> 03:32.712
is by getting my hands
on her phone.

03:32.712 --> 03:34.381
- What motive
could she possibly have

03:34.381 --> 03:35.757
for wanting him
to kill himself?

03:35.757 --> 03:37.467
- That's what I want
to find out.

03:39.803 --> 03:40.846
- Mm...

03:40.846 --> 03:42.347
okay, I'll get you a warrant,

03:42.347 --> 03:43.932
but do not push me

03:43.932 --> 03:45.934
if you find out
there's no there-there.

03:47.018 --> 03:48.687
You're welcome.

03:48.687 --> 03:49.896
- Thank you.

04:04.870 --> 04:07.164
- Hi.

04:07.164 --> 04:09.958
- Hi.

04:09.958 --> 04:13.128
Oh, I'm meeting a friend.

04:14.546 --> 04:17.299
Uh, Nat, I'll text you later.
- Okay, bye.

04:18.592 --> 04:20.510
- Bye, Cassie.
- Bye.

04:29.478 --> 04:30.604
- So are you--
- So how have you--

04:30.604 --> 04:32.272
- Oh, sorry, sorry. You go.

04:32.272 --> 04:35.150
- Yeah, no, I was just
gonna, um,

04:35.150 --> 04:36.985
ask how you're doing.

04:40.739 --> 04:43.742
- You know, I'm...I'm okay.

04:45.285 --> 04:47.496
It's hard to sleep.

04:47.496 --> 04:51.958
Nighttime was kind of our time,
me and Conrad.

04:53.794 --> 04:55.587
It's really sweet of you
to ask.

04:58.298 --> 04:59.758
Now that the fundraiser's over,
you know,

04:59.758 --> 05:03.470
I'm just trying to figure out
what to do next, you know,

05:03.470 --> 05:05.138
for Conrad.

05:05.138 --> 05:06.973
Like, I'm trying
to be there for his family,

05:06.973 --> 05:11.186
you know, for his mom.

05:11.186 --> 05:15.482
- Um...so you know
that text you sent me?

05:19.110 --> 05:21.696
- Which text?

05:21.696 --> 05:23.490
- About that night?

05:23.490 --> 05:26.201
- Oh, yeah.

05:26.201 --> 05:28.870
I don't know why I said that.

05:30.956 --> 05:33.542
Um...

05:33.542 --> 05:36.753
everything with Conrad
was really complicated,

05:36.753 --> 05:38.922
you know, obviously.

05:38.922 --> 05:41.925
Um, he was just so sad,

05:41.925 --> 05:43.969
and he didn't really feel like
he could talk to anyone,

05:43.969 --> 05:46.221
except me, of course.

05:46.221 --> 05:47.806
- Yeah, I mean, it was a lot
for you--

05:47.806 --> 05:49.558
- Which was okay, you know?

05:49.558 --> 05:52.477
Obviously, 'cause I loved him,
and...

05:52.477 --> 05:54.479
but I just wish
that his family knew

05:54.479 --> 05:56.648
that I was there for them too,

05:56.648 --> 05:58.233
that they can open up to me.

05:58.233 --> 06:00.610
But also wish
that somebody would

06:00.610 --> 06:01.987
care about how I'm feeling.

06:01.987 --> 06:03.655
You know, if anyone...
- Well, I care--

06:03.655 --> 06:04.781
- Wants to ask how I'm doing...

06:04.781 --> 06:05.824
- Michelle.
- Or how I'm feeling.

06:05.824 --> 06:08.159
- Michelle, stop.

06:08.159 --> 06:10.537
I'm asking if you're okay.

06:10.537 --> 06:12.664
- Right.

06:12.664 --> 06:15.792
Of course. I know. I'm--

06:15.792 --> 06:17.502
I'm sorry. So sorry.

06:17.502 --> 06:18.795
- No,
you don't have to be sorry.

06:18.795 --> 06:21.298
I just--
- Yeah.

06:21.298 --> 06:23.216
I know.
- Okay.

06:23.216 --> 06:24.968
- You're right. I'm sorry.

06:24.968 --> 06:26.303
- No.

06:31.558 --> 06:33.602
- You're such a good friend,
Natalie.

06:33.602 --> 06:35.145
Thank you
for being here for me.

06:46.948 --> 06:49.117
What?
I haven't.

06:49.117 --> 06:50.910
- You did!
Oh, my God, come on, Nat.

06:50.910 --> 06:52.162
That is not true.

06:52.162 --> 06:54.080
- The night
at Danny's graduation party?

06:54.080 --> 06:55.957
Okay, yes. Okay.

06:55.957 --> 06:57.250
- Yeah!
- Okay, okay, I forgot.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.085
Okay, okay, me next.

06:59.085 --> 07:02.380
Um, never have I ever...

07:04.591 --> 07:06.217
Had sex on the beach.

07:10.639 --> 07:14.976
- Um, excuse me, what?
- What?

07:14.976 --> 07:17.312
- Well, it wasn't sex,
so actually, never mind.

07:17.312 --> 07:19.397
- No, no, no, no, no.
You put a finger down.

07:19.397 --> 07:22.400
You have to tell the story.
Come on.

07:22.400 --> 07:24.194
We're waiting.

07:24.194 --> 07:26.988
It was just this guy
I met in Florida

07:26.988 --> 07:28.323
a few months ago.

07:28.323 --> 07:30.659
We, you know, fooled around.

07:30.659 --> 07:33.203
Details, bitch.

07:33.203 --> 07:37.248
Did you just, like, make out,
or did you go down on him?

07:37.248 --> 07:39.793
Did he go down on you?
Cassie.

07:39.793 --> 07:41.961
- Yeah, he did that.

07:41.961 --> 07:43.880
- Oh, my God.

07:43.880 --> 07:45.965
How come you never told?
Michelle.

07:45.965 --> 07:48.885
- Maybe 'cause she knew you'd
start third-degreeing her.

07:50.553 --> 07:54.474
- Oh, it's officially
getting hot in here.

07:54.474 --> 07:58.144
Natalia, shall we take a loop?
Sure.

08:00.355 --> 08:01.606
You coming?

08:01.606 --> 08:04.234
- I'm good.
I'll let the boys come to me.

08:06.027 --> 08:09.447
- Never have I ever wanted
to be part of that clique.

08:10.573 --> 08:13.159
- You know, they're just...

08:13.159 --> 08:16.996
- Oh, trust me, I know.

08:16.996 --> 08:19.457
I have friends like that
back at my school.

08:22.460 --> 08:23.962
Everyone's always so worried

08:23.962 --> 08:26.756
about the dudes
being mean to us.

08:26.756 --> 08:29.634
Meanwhile, we're over here
tearing each other's hair out.

08:30.969 --> 08:33.012
Girls are the worst.

08:33.012 --> 08:34.806
- Some girls are.

08:37.350 --> 08:40.270
I almost didn't come
on this trip.

08:40.270 --> 08:41.479
- And miss the Canada Cup

08:41.479 --> 08:43.815
International
Softball Championship?

08:47.485 --> 08:49.821
You're glad you came
now, though, right?

08:51.990 --> 08:53.867
- Yeah.

08:53.867 --> 08:55.118
Yeah, I am.

08:56.995 --> 08:58.204
- Me too.

09:01.958 --> 09:06.129
So tell me more about
this scandalous beach affair.

09:06.129 --> 09:08.048
- Oh, my God, it wasn't.

09:08.048 --> 09:09.424
- Sure, sure.

09:11.009 --> 09:15.722
- We texted a few times,
but he kind of disappeared.

09:15.722 --> 09:19.225
- Never have I ever taken you
for a one-night stand girl.

09:20.310 --> 09:24.105
- Babe, I'm full of surprises.

09:54.219 --> 09:56.387
You done?

09:56.387 --> 09:57.597
- No, sir.

10:04.395 --> 10:09.317
The last run for you,
for a while, anyway, yeah?

10:09.317 --> 10:11.611
You feel good?

10:11.611 --> 10:14.030
Being out here this year?
Did you have a good time?

10:16.866 --> 10:19.160
- Yeah.
- Good.

10:19.160 --> 10:22.580
You know, going back to school,

10:22.580 --> 10:25.625
back to your mom's

10:25.625 --> 10:29.254
after the long runs, it--

10:29.254 --> 10:34.008
it might be--might be tricky
for a little bit.

10:34.008 --> 10:36.594
But you'll get used to it.

10:36.594 --> 10:37.971
Yeah?

10:41.724 --> 10:44.644
All right, back at it.
- Yes, sir.

11:13.131 --> 11:14.799
There he is!

11:17.427 --> 11:19.721
There's the son
of Mattapoisett.

11:19.721 --> 11:22.140
Did you enjoy your last run?
- Eh.

11:22.140 --> 11:24.934
- All right, you guys, come on.

11:24.934 --> 11:26.853
Party's over.
You're still on the clock.

11:26.853 --> 11:29.230
I don't want
to have to call your wives

11:29.230 --> 11:31.107
and explain why you're
fucking passed out on my dock.

11:31.107 --> 11:33.234
You, put down the beer.
Come on.

11:33.234 --> 11:34.569
Look at the slack here.

11:35.403 --> 11:36.446
Coil it up, now.

11:38.740 --> 11:40.325
All right, back at it, boys.

12:25.954 --> 12:27.997
- Oh, Christ.

12:29.332 --> 12:30.458
Holly.

12:33.253 --> 12:35.880
God damn it, drop it!

12:35.880 --> 12:37.215
Drop it!

12:39.425 --> 12:41.052
Inside.

13:02.198 --> 13:04.450

<i>But David did not wallow</i>

13:04.450 --> 13:07.954
and fast and weep.

13:07.954 --> 13:10.665
He stood, washed,

13:10.665 --> 13:13.918
and fed
because he trusted the Lord.

13:14.919 --> 13:16.546
And David says...

13:18.047 --> 13:20.466
"I shall go to him,

13:20.466 --> 13:23.052
but he will not return to me."

13:23.052 --> 13:25.221
Because he knew they would
one day meet again...

13:25.221 --> 13:27.432
In heaven.

13:30.059 --> 13:32.937
- Put away the goddamn phones.

13:37.859 --> 13:41.154
We announce our faith
as we say, "I believe..."

13:42.030 --> 13:44.323
<i>- What are you thinking?</i>
- Huh?

13:44.323 --> 13:46.075
Usual?

13:46.075 --> 13:47.493
- Uh, yes.

13:49.829 --> 13:52.040
Here you go.

13:52.040 --> 13:53.291
You guys want
a couple of rolls?

13:53.291 --> 13:54.959
- Don't know why I even look.

13:56.794 --> 13:58.629
Thanks.

13:58.629 --> 14:00.256
- Thanks.

14:00.256 --> 14:02.592
- You guys speak
in full sentences on that boat?

14:02.592 --> 14:04.510
- Not if we don't have to.

14:04.510 --> 14:05.970
- Oh, cut it out.

14:05.970 --> 14:07.263
Whoo!

14:08.723 --> 14:10.558
- I'm glad you're back.
I missed you.

14:11.392 --> 14:13.603
- It was just a three-week run.

14:13.603 --> 14:16.147
- Yeah, well, three weeks can
feel like forever sometimes.

14:17.857 --> 14:20.818
Now you're back-back
and you're home, for good.

14:21.694 --> 14:23.571
- For now, I guess.

14:24.947 --> 14:27.700
- How was it?
Was it fun?

14:27.700 --> 14:29.911
- It's not really fun.

14:29.911 --> 14:33.706
It was--you know, it was work.

14:34.665 --> 14:37.543
- And how was it with your dad?
Everything okay?

14:37.543 --> 14:39.128
- Yeah.

14:43.382 --> 14:44.967
Here we go.

14:46.427 --> 14:47.553
Here we go.

14:47.553 --> 14:48.554
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

14:48.554 --> 14:50.223
All right, enjoy.

14:50.223 --> 14:52.475
Listen, I'm not mad
or anything,

14:52.475 --> 14:54.102
but we need to talk
about something.

14:54.102 --> 14:56.395
- Okay.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.523
- I found some dope
in your room.

15:01.901 --> 15:04.112
We talked about this.
I don't want it in the house.

15:05.905 --> 15:07.698
Especially around your sisters.

15:10.576 --> 15:12.829
If I find it again,
we're gonna have a problem.

15:14.038 --> 15:16.207
You're their big brother.

15:16.207 --> 15:18.501
It's your responsibility
to set a good example.

15:22.839 --> 15:24.799
What?

15:24.799 --> 15:26.801
- Nothing.
You're right. I get it.

15:28.094 --> 15:29.846
No more dope.

15:29.846 --> 15:31.848
- Pinkie swear?

15:39.522 --> 15:40.982
What?

15:40.982 --> 15:42.191
Not even a grunt this time?

15:57.123 --> 15:59.375
Michelle.

15:59.375 --> 16:00.585
I'm Detective Gordon.

16:00.585 --> 16:03.504
Uh, just need to ask you
a couple of questions.

16:03.504 --> 16:06.632
You're, uh--you're 18, correct?

16:06.632 --> 16:08.092
- Yeah.
- Right.

16:08.092 --> 16:10.845
So, uh, you can talk to me
on your own.

16:10.845 --> 16:12.680
Come on.

16:21.898 --> 16:24.358
So the reason why
I came out here is because

16:24.358 --> 16:27.278
I'm looking into Conrad Roy's
unfortunate passing.

16:28.362 --> 16:31.574
That, um--that fundraiser
you threw for him,

16:31.574 --> 16:34.076
that was--that was nice.

16:35.453 --> 16:36.621
We learned you did
a lot of nice things

16:36.621 --> 16:40.333
to help Conrad
and to help his family.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.919
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

16:42.919 --> 16:44.462
We determined
that you probably had

16:44.462 --> 16:46.631
a lot of contact with him.

16:46.631 --> 16:48.049
- Yeah.

16:48.049 --> 16:52.220
- Maybe even right up until
pretty close to the time

16:52.220 --> 16:55.348
in which maybe he stopped
having contact with anybody?

16:56.349 --> 16:58.476
- Um...

16:58.476 --> 17:00.061
yeah.

17:00.061 --> 17:02.355
- Did you have contact
with him that day,

17:02.355 --> 17:03.898
right up until he passed?

17:05.233 --> 17:06.692
- I don't think so.

17:08.402 --> 17:09.862
- Did he tell you
he was gonna do that

17:09.862 --> 17:11.072
or anything like that?

17:15.368 --> 17:18.204
- He'd been talking about it
for a while.

17:18.204 --> 17:22.875
He told me that nobody would
be able to help him, and...

17:22.875 --> 17:24.835
we were talking that night,

17:24.835 --> 17:26.587
and, like, the phone cut off,

17:26.587 --> 17:28.714
but I didn't think
anything of it.

17:31.926 --> 17:33.386
- Okay.

17:33.386 --> 17:35.972
Is--is that your phone?

17:35.972 --> 17:37.390
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

17:47.108 --> 17:49.485
All right, so, um,

17:49.485 --> 17:51.404
I've got a warrant
for this phone.

17:53.322 --> 17:55.616
- Wait, you're taking my phone?

17:55.616 --> 17:56.826
- Yeah.

17:56.826 --> 17:58.995
I'm gonna accompany you
to your home,

17:58.995 --> 18:00.705
and I'm gonna collect
your computer

18:00.705 --> 18:02.373
and any other device

18:02.373 --> 18:04.000
that might connect
to the internet.

18:05.334 --> 18:07.044
- Mm.
- Do you understand?

18:08.588 --> 18:10.631
Mm.

18:10.631 --> 18:13.884
- Okay.
You're gonna come with me.

18:51.339 --> 18:52.923
I think I have the right
to know why our daughter

18:52.923 --> 18:55.384
just got escorted home
in a police cruiser!

18:55.384 --> 18:57.595
- Lower your voice.
- Dad, please.

18:57.595 --> 18:59.764
I'm Conrad's girlfriend.

18:59.764 --> 19:00.890
Of course
they're reaching out to me.

19:00.890 --> 19:02.391
They're looking for answers.

19:02.391 --> 19:04.685
- What answers could you
possibly give the police?

19:04.685 --> 19:06.687
They had a warrant, Michelle.

19:06.687 --> 19:08.898
- He didn't talk
to anybody else.

19:08.898 --> 19:11.108
I'm the only one who knows
why he really did it.

19:11.108 --> 19:13.235
- Well, why did he do it?

19:13.235 --> 19:15.363
- He was too bright
for this world.

19:15.363 --> 19:18.074
He was my star,
and he left too soon.

19:18.074 --> 19:20.451
- Is that from <i>Glee?</i>

19:20.451 --> 19:22.119
- Mind your own
fucking business, Hayden.

19:22.119 --> 19:23.871
- Hey,
watch your language!
- Michelle.

19:23.871 --> 19:26.207
- I can't believe you guys
are attacking me like this,

19:26.207 --> 19:27.958
after everything
I've been through.

19:27.958 --> 19:29.418
Leave me alone!

19:30.836 --> 19:32.880
Michelle!

20:11.460 --> 20:13.295
You are such a dork.

20:13.295 --> 20:15.589
- I is what I is.

20:15.589 --> 20:17.925
I can't believe
you've never seen this.

20:17.925 --> 20:20.803
- Ah, just never got into it.

20:20.803 --> 20:22.096
So that's the main couple.

20:22.096 --> 20:24.724
- Rachel and Finn.
- Mm.

20:24.724 --> 20:27.017
- They just put off
their engagement in real life.

20:27.017 --> 20:29.395
- Mm, the will they,
won't they?

20:29.395 --> 20:32.064
Television necessity.

20:32.064 --> 20:33.357
Are those two together?

20:33.357 --> 20:36.360
- Yeah--or not yet.

20:36.360 --> 20:40.448
They start off as friends,
best friends,

20:40.448 --> 20:42.450
and then
they eventually get together.

20:43.868 --> 20:45.745
- That's rad.

20:45.745 --> 20:47.997
I'm surprised
the show goes there.

20:47.997 --> 20:49.749
