all right.

25:38.996 --> 25:40.456
So I'm on my shift.

25:40.456 --> 25:41.665
ER rounds this week,

25:41.665 --> 25:43.667
so, you know,
it's a fucking nightmare.

25:43.667 --> 25:46.754
And this skinny,
nervous-looking guy comes in.

25:46.754 --> 25:49.757
Says he's got a stomachache
but doesn't want to say why,

25:49.757 --> 25:53.802
but I can tell he's--you know,
he's walking kind of funny.

25:53.802 --> 25:56.680
So we get him under the X-ray.

25:56.680 --> 25:58.557
The doc puts up the images,

25:58.557 --> 26:01.727
and...there it is.

26:03.103 --> 26:05.981
A toilet brush.

26:05.981 --> 26:07.232
- Where?

26:07.232 --> 26:08.484
His ass.

26:12.321 --> 26:15.699
- No way.

26:15.699 --> 26:19.286
- I just have
so many questions.

26:19.286 --> 26:20.996
Like a fucking chimney sweep.

26:39.556 --> 26:41.141
Stop it.

27:29.648 --> 27:30.983
There she is.

27:36.655 --> 27:37.906
- Hi, Conrad.

27:40.534 --> 27:43.954
- Finally, she speaks.

27:43.954 --> 27:46.665
- Me?
I've been right here.

27:46.665 --> 27:48.125
- What are you doing now?

27:49.668 --> 27:52.129
- Playing basketball.

27:52.129 --> 27:54.590
What are you doing?

27:54.590 --> 27:55.924
- What do you think?

27:59.011 --> 28:02.472
- How are you?
- Meh.

28:02.472 --> 28:05.017
Headed back to school.

28:05.017 --> 28:07.060
In a completely different
class now

28:07.060 --> 28:08.520
'cause of my year off.

28:08.520 --> 28:10.898
Back at my mom's.

28:10.898 --> 28:12.232
It's weird.
I don't know.

28:15.193 --> 28:16.403
Tell me.

28:18.780 --> 28:21.909
- It feels like my brain
works differently now.

28:23.702 --> 28:25.662
The boat is all guys
my dad's age,

28:25.662 --> 28:28.749
and I figured out
how to talk to them,

28:28.749 --> 28:33.420
but now I don't know
how to be a kid anymore.

28:35.380 --> 28:38.133
- That's because
you're an old soul, Conrad.

28:41.845 --> 28:45.223
- On the boat,
everything made sense.

28:45.223 --> 28:46.975
Every day,
I knew what I was doing.

28:48.310 --> 28:49.686
You never felt like...

28:51.396 --> 28:52.898
You didn't know
what was coming.

28:52.898 --> 28:54.483
- Like a checklist.

28:56.735 --> 28:58.779
- Exactly.
- That sounds amazing.

28:58.779 --> 29:00.072
I wish I had that

29:00.072 --> 29:01.990
but for, like, school
and friends and whatever.

29:03.575 --> 29:05.786
- Yes.

29:05.786 --> 29:08.330
- What if you had
a checklist for life?

29:08.330 --> 29:09.998
Like, you just did the thing,

29:09.998 --> 29:12.668
move on to the next thing,
everything easy.

29:12.668 --> 29:13.877
Check, check, check.

29:13.877 --> 29:15.587
- That's what I'm saying.

29:15.587 --> 29:18.215
On the water, there's order.

29:18.215 --> 29:19.883
Calm.

29:19.883 --> 29:21.259
'Cause you know what's coming,

29:21.259 --> 29:23.220
even if it's, like,
a storm or something.

29:24.930 --> 29:28.141
Boats are simple...

29:28.141 --> 29:29.851
but complicated.

29:29.851 --> 29:31.979
They built them
with their hands,

29:31.979 --> 29:35.607
and we have to work them
with our hands.

29:35.607 --> 29:37.526
It's tactile.

29:37.526 --> 29:38.777
- Tactile?

29:42.030 --> 29:44.533
- Yeah, like, physical.

29:47.160 --> 29:49.746
- I get it.

29:49.746 --> 29:53.750
Like something to hold on to.

29:53.750 --> 29:56.086
Move your body.
Get out of your head.

29:57.462 --> 29:58.630
- Yeah, exactly.

30:02.634 --> 30:05.137
Hey, do you remember the pier?

30:05.137 --> 30:06.680
- Yeah.

30:09.266 --> 30:10.392
- Sand.

30:10.392 --> 30:11.852
- Hand.

30:11.852 --> 30:13.020
- Band.

30:17.065 --> 30:18.483
- Why now?

30:20.402 --> 30:21.778
- Why...

30:24.740 --> 30:27.325
- You never came
to say goodbye that day.

30:27.325 --> 30:28.785
You just disappeared.

30:31.580 --> 30:32.748
- I know.

30:34.708 --> 30:35.709
I'm sorry.

30:38.754 --> 30:41.131
I fucked up.
It's my fault.

30:41.131 --> 30:42.758
It's always my fault.

30:45.969 --> 30:47.262
- So why now?

30:48.805 --> 30:50.807
- I miss talking to you
at 3:00 a. m.

30:53.477 --> 30:54.978
Did you miss me?

31:00.484 --> 31:02.611
Are we doing
the "no sleeping" thing again?

31:05.739 --> 31:07.491
- Pretty predictable, huh?

31:07.491 --> 31:09.785
- I wouldn't say that.

31:28.720 --> 31:30.430
Kind of worried about you.

31:32.140 --> 31:33.517
The not sleeping.

31:33.517 --> 31:34.893
- Don't be.

31:35.977 --> 31:38.438
It just gets weird at night.

31:38.438 --> 31:40.023
Kind of hard to describe.

31:43.235 --> 31:44.402
- Try.

31:47.989 --> 31:50.659
- It's like...

31:50.659 --> 31:52.452
spinning.

31:52.452 --> 31:55.038
Or, like, a spinning feeling.

31:57.249 --> 31:59.668
It gets worse
when I close my eyes,

31:59.668 --> 32:01.044
when everything's quiet.

32:02.379 --> 32:04.506
It's like my thoughts
keep happening all at once,

32:04.506 --> 32:08.677
but I can't focus
on any one of them.

32:08.677 --> 32:11.429
So it just turns
into this massive spiral.

32:14.349 --> 32:16.726
So I just stay awake.

32:18.937 --> 32:20.897
- Have you thought
about talking to someone?

32:22.607 --> 32:24.609
- I started taking meds.

32:24.609 --> 32:25.944
Prozac.

32:25.944 --> 32:28.113
- Is it helping?

32:28.113 --> 32:29.322
- I don't know.

32:38.665 --> 32:40.375
I get scared sometimes.

32:43.587 --> 32:46.798
Never told anyone that before.

32:46.798 --> 32:48.800
- You can literally
tell me anything.

32:50.760 --> 32:52.387
I love you.

34:53.800 --> 34:56.052
- You okay?

34:57.304 --> 34:59.472
Can't turn
my goddamn brain off.

35:01.850 --> 35:03.768
You know, he promised me,

35:03.768 --> 35:06.062
after the first time.

35:06.062 --> 35:09.274
He promised he wouldn't do
anything like that ever again.

35:10.859 --> 35:14.195
And I must've asked him
a thousand times,

35:14.195 --> 35:16.865
"Are you okay?"

35:16.865 --> 35:20.076
And a thousand times,
he said, "Yeah."

35:23.538 --> 35:26.916
There was a minute today...

35:26.916 --> 35:29.377
when I forgot.

35:29.377 --> 35:31.546
Just a minute.

35:35.008 --> 35:38.970
And then I remembered,
and it was like he...

35:38.970 --> 35:41.514
he died all over again.

35:41.514 --> 35:44.142
And I feel guilty
all over again.

35:50.148 --> 35:51.608
Five minutes.

35:54.819 --> 35:55.820
What?

35:58.031 --> 36:00.742
- I was five minutes away
from that parking lot.

36:02.869 --> 36:06.164
I mean, why didn't he call me?

36:14.923 --> 36:17.801
- The hell is all this?

36:17.801 --> 36:20.512
- Oh, uh,
early birthday present

36:20.512 --> 36:23.473
from our friendly
neighborhood detective, Gordon.

36:23.473 --> 36:25.141
- The Roy case?

36:25.141 --> 36:27.435
- Phone records
from the Roy kid's phone

36:27.435 --> 36:31.272
and every text Carter sent
in the last two years.

36:32.982 --> 36:34.776
- "Hey, it's Michelle. LOL.

36:34.776 --> 36:37.654
You're gonna think I'm weird.
Ha-ha, don't be mad."

36:39.447 --> 36:41.074
How long have you been here?

36:41.074 --> 36:43.201
- Oh, like...

36:43.201 --> 36:45.453
three years, 14 hours.

36:45.453 --> 36:46.996
- Buy you a drink?

36:46.996 --> 36:49.499
- No, no, I should stay.
Thank you.

36:49.499 --> 36:53.712
- Katie, only bad work
happens after 10:00.

36:55.630 --> 36:57.215
Come on.

37:00.510 --> 37:03.555
We all said shitty things
in high school.

37:03.555 --> 37:07.559
I don't envy these kids.
Every word recorded.

37:07.559 --> 37:09.352
- Why, why did she lie
to her friends

37:09.352 --> 37:11.521
about not knowing
where Conrad was?

37:11.521 --> 37:12.897
- Mm-mm-mm.

37:12.897 --> 37:14.566
- You know who lies?
Guilty people.

37:14.566 --> 37:17.235
- You know who lies?
Teenagers.

37:18.236 --> 37:20.363
Six ball, corner.

37:20.363 --> 37:22.031
- It's not like I don't see
what's at stake here.

37:22.031 --> 37:25.910
I mean, if we tried this,
it would be precedent-setting.

37:25.910 --> 37:29.289
- Look, I get it.
You're hungry.

37:29.289 --> 37:31.416
Every case for you
is another rung on the ladder,

37:31.416 --> 37:34.586
so every case has to be
solid enough to stand on.

37:34.586 --> 37:37.797
Your future's
just dangling there,

37:37.797 --> 37:39.799
waiting to be snatched up.

37:41.342 --> 37:43.511
Eight ball, side.

37:45.638 --> 37:49.267
- Wait, how long
have I been drinking?

37:49.267 --> 37:50.268
- Your break.

38:04.532 --> 38:05.700
Huh.

38:08.161 --> 38:09.412
- I'm more of a solo,

38:09.412 --> 38:11.414
noncontact,
figure skating girl.

38:11.414 --> 38:15.084
- Here, it's all about...

38:15.084 --> 38:16.419
seeing the whole game.

38:17.670 --> 38:18.838
What do you see?

38:20.507 --> 38:22.717
- A bunch
of different-colored balls.

38:22.717 --> 38:26.679
- Okay, what happens if I hit
the nine in the corner?

38:26.679 --> 38:28.473
- It bounces off the wall.

38:28.473 --> 38:30.350
- Yeah, and when it lands,
I better be setting myself up

38:30.350 --> 38:32.310
for the 14
to hit the left side

38:32.310 --> 38:34.604
and then 10 after that
and so on.

38:34.604 --> 38:38.817
Every choice I make
has to be about the end goal.

38:38.817 --> 38:40.026
Doesn't look,
you know, so pretty

38:40.026 --> 38:41.444
when it's all out there
on the table,

38:41.444 --> 38:42.779
but when you put it together--

38:42.779 --> 38:43.988
- Wait.

38:48.117 --> 38:49.452
Thank you.
- Okay.

38:51.871 --> 38:53.998
- It's like you said,
seeing the whole table.

38:53.998 --> 38:56.459
I--I was only looking
at the texts

38:56.459 --> 38:57.669
that she sent to the kid.

38:57.669 --> 38:59.963
I didn't think
that her friends were...

39:02.757 --> 39:05.260
To Natalie something.

39:05.260 --> 39:07.011
A few weeks after the funeral.

39:07.011 --> 39:08.721
She told him
to get back in the truck.

39:08.721 --> 39:11.683
It is practically
a goddamn confession.

39:11.683 --> 39:13.226
- It's something.

39:13.226 --> 39:15.854
- You know, I'm gonna need
a second chair on this.

39:18.481 --> 39:20.358
What?

39:20.358 --> 39:21.776
- I just want to make sure
we do this

39:21.776 --> 39:23.486
because there's a case,

39:23.486 --> 39:25.363
not because
it's one of those rungs.

39:26.698 --> 39:28.783
- Well...

39:28.783 --> 39:30.076
it is, and it is.

39:32.287 --> 39:34.205
How are you gonna
get around the fact

39:34.205 --> 39:36.958
that assisted suicide
is not illegal?

39:36.958 --> 39:39.085
- I'll take that as a yes.

42:54.030 --> 42:56.407
The DA opened
an official investigation

42:56.407 --> 42:59.243
into your connection
with the death of Conrad Roy.

42:59.243 --> 43:00.953
- But I didn't do
anything wrong.

43:00.953 --> 43:02.580
- You think she'll go to jail?

43:02.580 --> 43:05.500
- I will do everything in
my power to make that happen.

43:07.752 --> 43:09.337
<i>We need motive.</i>

43:09.337 --> 43:10.755
An assisted suicide
is not illegal

43:10.755 --> 43:11.923
in the state of Massachusetts.

43:11.923 --> 43:13.591
- Right, but she isn't
assisting.

43:13.591 --> 43:14.592
She's masterminding.

43:14.592 --> 43:16.594
- I just wanted to help him.

43:16.594 --> 43:18.179
Maybe I should call your mom.

43:18.179 --> 43:20.890
- If you ever tell anyone
about me,

43:20.890 --> 43:23.726
I will never talk to you again!

43:23.726 --> 43:26.312
- Carter has waived her right
to a jury trial,

43:26.312 --> 43:27.688
<i>which means the judge alone</i>

43:27.688 --> 43:30.525
<i>will decide whether or not</i>
<i>she is guilty.</i>

43:30.525 --> 43:33.694
- Her behavior was wanton
and reckless.

43:33.694 --> 43:36.572
There are text
<i>messages, thousands of them.</i>

43:36.572 --> 43:38.825
- She told him to drink bleach.

43:40.618 --> 43:42.370
- The night of his death,

43:42.370 --> 43:45.248
did you tell him
to get back in the truck?

43:45.248 --> 43:46.624
- I loved him.

43:47.750 --> 43:49.502
- She knew him.

43:49.502 --> 43:51.671
<i>She knew he was depressed.</i>

43:51.671 --> 43:53.673
- Tried to help you
the best I could.

43:53.673 --> 43:55.967
<i>I could never</i>
<i>talk you out of it.</i>

43:55.967 --> 43:58.719
- She knew what it was like
to feel lonely.

43:58.719 --> 44:00.513
- There's no one left.

44:00.513 --> 44:02.932
Your Honor,
<i>this is not a homicide case.</i>

44:02.932 --> 44:04.809
- She put him in that car
that night.

44:04.809 --> 44:07.520
- She was 30 miles away.

44:07.520 --> 44:09.480
I should have
<i>been there for you.</i>
